package dev.cajeta.logging;

/**
 * Marks a class for an auto-synthesized logger — Cajeta's `@Slf4j`. The compiler
 * injects a `static Logger log = Log.defaultFor("pkg.Class")` member into any
 * class carrying `@Logged`, so a `log` handle is available with no boilerplate:
 *
 * ```cajeta
 * @Logged
 * public class CheckoutService {
 *     public void pay() {
 *         log.info("charged");            // `log` is synthesized — never declared
 *     }
 * }
 * ```
 *
 * The synthesized field is `static` (one logger per class, usable from static
 * methods, no per-instance cost), named for the annotated class, and configured
 * by `Log.defaultFor` (compact JSONL to stdout at INFO by default). Named
 * `@Logged` rather than `@Logger` so it stays distinct from the `Logger` facade
 * class it produces — the annotation marks a class as logging-enabled.
 *
 * NOTE: `@Logged` is wired in the cajeta-two compiler (annotation-driven field
 * synthesis); a toolchain without that support compiles the annotation as a
 * no-op (no `log` field), so use a compiler that ships the synthesis pass.
 */
public annotation Logged { }
